cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper describes the design and development of a deductive database system, LDL++, and discusses its functionality and integration with existing DBMSs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper introduces new nonmonotonic and nondeterministic constructs in LDL++ that extend its functionality, which are commonly used in AI applications. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses the model-theoretic and fixpoint semantics of LDL++, which are fundamental concepts in logic and reasoning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper describes the open architecture designed to support the new constructs and facilitate integration with existing applications, which is a software engineering concern. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the execution model of LDL++ and its language constructs, which are relevant to programming language design and implementation.
